# Next.js App Router

## Server vs Client

- **Default to Server Components** — no `"use client"` unless needed
- Add `"use client"` for: `useState`, `useEffect`, event handlers, browser APIs, third-party client-only libs

## Data & Metadata

- Export `metadata` or `generateMetadata` from layouts/pages
- Fetch in server components directly; avoid client-side fetch for initial page data
- Use `next/image` for images, `next/link` for internal navigation

```tsx
// ✅ Internal nav
import Link from "next/link";
<Link href="/about">About</Link>

// ❌ Full page reload for internal routes
<a href="/about">About</a>
```

## Performance

- Use `priority` on above-the-fold `Image` components
- Colocate loading UI in `loading.tsx`, errors in `error.tsx` when routes grow
- Lazy-load heavy client components with `dynamic()` from `next/dynamic`

## Breaking Changes

This project uses **Next.js 16** — consult `node_modules/next/dist/docs/01-app/` before implementing routing, caching, or config features.
